  <!-- ==================== SECTION 9: PLANNING PROCESS ==================== -->
  <section class="process fade-in">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="process-header">
        <div class="section-label">How It Works</div>
        <h2>From First Call To Last Dance</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="process-steps">
        <div class="process-step">
          <div class="process-step-number">01</div>
          <h3>Check Your Date</h3>
          <p>Use our quick form to tell us your preferred date, guest count, and what you are looking for. We will get back to you within 24 hours.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <div class="process-step-number">02</div>
          <h3>Discovery Call</h3>
          <p>A 15-minute call with Hugo to see if we are the right fit. No pressure, no hard sell - just an honest conversation about your wedding.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <div class="process-step-number">03</div>
          <h3>Visit The Venue</h3>
          <p>If it is a match, we will invite you in to see the space in person and talk through how your wedding would work in the building.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <div class="process-step-number">04</div>
          <h3>Your Proposal</h3>
          <p>A detailed proposal based on everything you have discussed - your menu, drinks, timeline, extras. One document, one total.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="process-step">
          <div class="process-step-number">05</div>
          <h3>Secure Your Date</h3>
          <p>A deposit secures your date. From there, your dedicated events team guides you through every decision until the big day.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style="text-align:center;">
        <a href="/check-your-date" class="btn btn-primary">Check Your Date - It Takes 30 Seconds</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ==================== SECTION 10: FAQs ==================== -->
  <section class="faqs fade-in">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="faqs-header">
        <div class="section-label">FAQs</div>
        <h2>Questions Couples Ask Us</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>How many guests can the venue hold?</span>
            <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">Up to 60 seated for dinner and up to 100 for standing receptions. We are an intimate venue - if you are planning for more than 60 seated guests, we are probably not the right fit, but we are happy to recommend alternatives.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>Can we hold our ceremony here?</span>
            <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">Yes. Civil ceremonies, humanist celebrations, and symbolic services all work beautifully in the space. Many couples choose to have their ceremony and reception in the same venue - it keeps the day flowing and means no transfers between locations.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>What time does the venue open and close?</span>
            <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">Standard hire runs from 3pm. Music finishes at 11pm and guests depart by 11:30pm. If you would like an earlier start - for getting-ready time, a morning ceremony, or a longer reception - earlier access is available from &pound;170 for a 2pm start.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>Is there a curfew for music?</span>
            <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">Music runs until 11pm. Our built-in sound system covers the full space - you can bring your own playlist, hire a DJ, or book a live band. No need for external speakers or AV hire.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>Can we bring our own suppliers?</span>
            <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">Our food, drinks, and coordination are all in-house - that is what makes the model work. For flowers, photography, entertainment, and other personal touches, you are welcome to bring whoever you like. We work with external suppliers regularly and are happy to recommend trusted partners.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>Do you cater for dietary requirements?</span>
            <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">Absolutely. Our kitchen handles vegetarian, vegan, gluten-free, halal, kosher, and other dietary needs as standard. Just let us know during planning and we will build it into your menu.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>What is included in the venue hire fee?</span>
            <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">Exclusive hire of the entire building, your dedicated on-day coordinator, full events team, all staffing, furniture, decor, tableware basics, and our built-in sound and lighting system. See the Everything Included section above for the full list.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>How far in advance should we book?</span>
            <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">Most couples book 8-9 months ahead of their wedding date. Peak season Saturdays (May - September) fill fastest. If you have a specific date in mind, check availability sooner rather than later.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

